com.identityx.clientSDK.repositories

Class BaseRepository<T extends IRestResource,U extends RestCollection<T>,V extends QueryHolder>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.identityx.clientSDK.repositories.BaseRepository<T,U,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of an entity. Entities implement IRestResource
    U - type of an entity collection. Entity collections implement RestCollection
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ApplicationRepository, AuditRepository, AuthenticationRequestRepository, AuthenticatorRepository, AuthenticatorTypeRepository, PolicyRepository, RegistrationChallengeRepository, RegistrationRepository, RoleRepository, SessionTokenRepository, SponsorshipRepository, SystemAuthenticatorTypeRepository, TenantRepository, TokenRepository, UserRepository

    public class BaseRepository<T extends IRestResource,U extends RestCollection<T>,V extends QueryHolder>
extends Object
    Base class for creating a repository for a particular entity type. A repository is a client abstraction used to access a set of Rest services related to an entity type.
